# AuctionHub — Full-Fledge Feature Roadmap

Based on a thorough audit of your current codebase (models, routes, controllers, and frontend pages), here's what's built, what's missing, and what would make this a truly production-ready auction platform.

---

## ✅ Already Built

| Feature | Status |
|---|---|
| Auth (Register / Login / JWT) | ✅ Done |
| Auction CRUD + Image Upload | ✅ Done |
| Real-time Bidding (Socket.io) | ✅ Done |
| Anti-snipe + Duplicate Bid Prevention | ✅ Done |
| Admin Approval Workflow | ✅ Done |
| Watchlist | ✅ Done |
| Bid History | ✅ Done |
| Activity Log | ✅ Done |
| Seller Reviews (per-auction) | ✅ Done |
| Site Platform Reviews | ✅ Done (added today) |
| Landing Page Sections (About, Contact, Reviews) | ✅ Done (added today) |
| Top 3 Auctions on Landing | ✅ Done (added today) |

---

## 🔴 High Priority — Core Auction Functionality

### 1. User Profile Page ✅ Done
**What's missing:** You have `avatar`, `bio`, `location`, `phone`, `totalBids`, `totalWins` fields in the User model but **zero frontend UI** for editing or viewing them.

- View own profile (stats, bids won, listings created)
- Edit name, avatar, bio, location, phone
- Public seller profile page (visible to buyers)

### 2. Notifications System
**What's missing:** No in-app notification center.

- "You've been outbid" — alert users when someone places a higher bid
- "Auction ending soon" — 1 hour / 15 min reminder
- "You won an auction"
- "Your listing was approved/rejected"
- Mark as read / clear all

> Backend model already partially implied via `Activity.js` — notifications could share this layer.

### 3. Payment Integration ✅ Done
**What's missing:** There is NO payment flow. After winning an auction, nothing happens.

- Stripe / Razorpay checkout flow for winners
- Payment status stored on auction (`payment: { status, transactionId, paidAt }`)
- Invoice / receipt generation

### 4. Winner Flow (Post-Auction) ✅ Done
**What's missing:** Auction ends → winner has no next steps.

- "Congratulations, you won!" page
- Shipping address collection
- Order tracking status
- Seller marking item as "shipped"

---

## 🟠 Medium Priority — UX & Engagement

### 5. Advanced Search & Filters ✅ Done
**What's there:** Basic `/search` page exists.

**What's missing:**
- Filter by price range (slider)
- Filter by category, condition, location
- Sort by: ending soonest, price low/high, most bids
- Saved search alerts ("notify me when a Rolex goes up")

### 6. Auction Categories Page ✅ Done
**What's missing:** No dedicated browsing by category.

- `/category/watches`, `/category/art` etc.
- Category landing pages with hero images
- Item count per category

### 7. Seller Dashboard Enhancement ✅ Done
**What's there:** Basic dashboard exists.

**What's missing:**
- Earnings analytics (total earned, pending payments)
- Performance stats (views per listing, bid-to-view ratio)
- Manage active listings (edit/cancel)

### 8. Buyer Dashboard Enhancement ✅ Done
**What's there:** Basic dashboard.

**What's missing:**
- "Auctions I'm Winning" vs "Auctions I've Lost"
- Watchlist section with "Ending Soon" alerts
- Purchase history / orders

### 9. Featured / Promoted Auctions
- Sellers can pay to "feature" their listing on the homepage
- Featured badge / spotlight carousel on Landing page

---

## 🟡 Nice-to-Have — Trust & Safety

### 10. Email Verification & Password Reset ✅ Done
**What's missing:** `isVerified` exists on User model but no email flow exists.

- Verification email on sign-up (Nodemailer / SendGrid)
- "Forgot Password" → email link → reset form

### 11. Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)
- TOTP-based (Google Authenticator) or SMS OTP

### 12. Identity Verification for Sellers
**What's there:** `isVerified` flag.

**What's missing:**
- KYC document upload flow
- Admin review of seller verification
- "Verified Seller" badge on listings

### 13. Report & Flag System ✅ Done
- Report a suspicious listing
- Report a user for bad behavior
- Admin moderation queue for flagged content

### 14. Dispute Resolution ✅ Done
- Buyer raises dispute ("item not as described")
- Seller responds
- Admin mediates

---

## 🔵 Scaling & Polish

### 15. Real-time Bid Feed / Live Ticker ✅ Done
- A live ticker on the homepage showing recent bids across the platform
- "Someone just bid $1,200 on Vintage Rolex Submariner" notifications

### 16. SEO & Meta Tags
- Dynamic `<title>` and `<meta description>` per auction page
- Open Graph tags for social sharing

### 17. Mobile Responsiveness Audit
- Ensure all pages (Dashboard, AuctionDetail, CreateListing) are fully responsive
- Consider a mobile-first navbar with a hamburger menu

### 18. Auction Scheduling
**What's there:** `startDate` field exists but isn't used on the frontend.

- Sellers schedule auctions to start at a future date/time
- "Upcoming Auctions" section on homepage

### 19. Auto-Extend (Anti-Snipe) Visibility
- Show a timer badge: "Bid placed — extended by 5 min" in real-time on the UI

### 20. Dark/Light Mode Toggle
- Theme toggle in the navbar

---

## Priority Order Recommendation

```
P0 (Ship these first — platform is incomplete without them)
  → User Profile Page
  → Payment Integration (Stripe)
  → Winner / Post-Auction Flow

P1 (Strongly improves trust & engagement)
  → Notifications System
  → Email Verification + Password Reset
  → Advanced Search & Filters

P2 (Differentiators)
  → Seller Identity Verification
  → Category Browse Pages
  → Dispute Resolution
  → Featured Auctions
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **The most critical missing piece is the Payment & Winner Flow.** Right now, an auction ends and nothing happens — there's no way for a winner to pay, and no way for a seller to know. This is the #1 gap between "demo project" and "real product".

> [!TIP]
> **Notifications** can be built quickly using your existing Socket.io setup — you already have a real-time channel. Just emit events to specific user rooms on bid events and auction endings.
